The last Corona Sunsets Festival took place in 2019 and featured the likes of Fisher, Nora en Pure, Prince Kaybee, Shimza, Bantwanas, Goodluck, Abby Nurock and more. Festival-goers can expect a similarly star-studded line-up of artists, to be announced soon.Clifton’s Oval Field, will once again host the show. Promising sensational outdoor moments with friends, incredible music, and the ultimate sunset moment over the Atlantic Ocean. The show will also present locally sourced and organic craft food and art vendors as well as Corona merchandise for sale.“It’s been an incredible summer of Chasing Sunsets events and what better way to wrap up the summer than to save the best for last with the return of the biggest Corona Sunsets Festival yet,” says Melanie Nicholson, Corona SA Marketing Manager.“Due to the fact that there are still protocols to be observed, we will of course have strict COVID regulations in place. While we are normalising, we are very aware of the level of responsibility that comes with holding well-attended events and we will ensure that there are no complications or setbacks,” says event organizer, Shaun Duwe.General Access tickets cost R660. For tickets and more information visit: Corona.Howler.co.zaAnyone with a valid ticket from Corona Sunsets Festival 2020 can still redeem their ticket for this event. Keep an eye out for further information.